ures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">para cualquier complejo<span>&nbsp;</span><i>z</i><span>&nbsp;</span>y<span>&nbsp;</span><i>w</i>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Por definiciÃ³n, la funciÃ³n distancia queda como sigue<span>&nbsp;</span><i>d</i>(<i>z</i>,<span>&nbsp;</span><i>w</i>) = |<i>z</i><span>&nbsp;</span>-<span>&nbsp;</span><i>w</i>| y nos provee de un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Espacio_m%C3%A9trico\" title=\"Espacio mÃ©trico\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">espacio mÃ©trico</a><span>&nbsp;</span>con los complejos gracias al que se puede hablar de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/L%C3%ADmite_matem%C3%A1tico\" title=\"LÃ­mite matemÃ¡tico\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">lÃ­mites</a><span>&nbsp;</span>y<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continuidad_(matem%C3%A1tica)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Continuidad (matemÃ¡tica)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">continuidad</a>. La suma, la resta, la multiplicaciÃ³n y la divisiÃ³n de complejos son operaciones continuas. Si no se dice lo contrario, se asume que Ã©sta es la mÃ©trica usada en los nÃºmeros complejos.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Argumento_o_fase\">Argumento o fase</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=N%C3%BAmero_complejo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Argumento o fase\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"noprint AP rellink\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.32px;\">ArtÃ­culo principal:</span><span>&nbsp;</span><i style=\"font-style: normal;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argumento_(an%C3%A1lisis_complejo)\" title=\"Argumento (anÃ¡lisis complejo)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Argumento (anÃ¡lisis complejo)</a></i></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">El<span>&nbsp;</span><i><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argumento_(an%C3%A1lisis_complejo)\" title=\"Argumento (anÃ¡lisis complejo)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">argumento</a><span>&nbsp;</span>principal</i><span>&nbsp;</span>o<span>&nbsp;</span><i>fase</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de un nÃºmero complejo genÃ©rico<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle z=x+yi,}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7963177ec380df2c4b913deb452522c15dafa43a\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"z=x+yi,\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 10.702ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>(siendo<span>&nbsp;</span><i>x</i>=Re(<i>z</i>) e<span>&nbsp;</span><i>y</i>=Im(<i>z</i>)) es el Ã¡ngulo<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle phi }</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/72b1f30316670aee6270a28334bdf4f5072cdde4\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\" phi\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 1.385ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>que forman el eje de abscisas<span>&nbsp;</span><i>OX</i><span>&nbsp;</span>y el vector<span>&nbsp;</span><i>OM</i>, con M(<i>x</i>,<i>y</i>). Viene dado por la siguiente expresiÃ³n:</p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle phi =operatorname {Arg} (z)=operatorname {atan2} (y,x)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9bf46275a81ecd18f13a045bcfc294af5a15979f\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"phi =operatorname {Arg}(z)=operatorname {atan2}(y,x)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 25.31ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">donde atan2(y,x) es la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funci%C3%B3n_arcotangente\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"FunciÃ³n arcotangente\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciÃ³n arcotangente</a><span>&nbsp;</span>definida para los cuatro cuadrantes:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle operatorname {atan2} (y,x)={egin{cases}arctan left({frac {y}{x}}\r\night)&amp;qquad x&gt;0arctan left({frac {y}{x}}\r\night)+pi &amp;qquad ygeq 0,x&lt;0arctan left({frac {y}{x}}\r\night)-pi &amp;qquad y&lt;0,x&lt;0+{frac {pi }{2}}&amp;qquad y&gt;0,x=0-{frac {pi }{2}}&amp;qquad y&lt;0,x=0{	ext{indefinido}}&amp;qquad y=0,x=0end{cases}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/fdea743a3c598491f190fcb7a7d69ec0a633b0b8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"operatorname {atan2}(y,x)={egin{cases}arctan left({frac  yx}\r\night)&amp;qquad x>0arctan left({frac  yx}\r\night)+pi &amp;qquad ygeq 0,x<0arctan left({frac  yx}\r\night)-pi &amp;qquad y<0,x<0+{frac  {pi }{2}}&amp;qquad y>0,x=0-{frac  {pi }{2}}&amp;qquad y<0,x=0{	ext{indefinido}}&amp;qquad y=0,x=0end{cases}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -8.956ex; display: inline-block; margin-bottom: -0.215ex; width: 50.482ex; height: 19.509ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">O tambiÃ©n:<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle operatorname {atan2} (y,x)={frac {pi }{2}}operatorname {sgn} (y)-arctan left({frac {x}{y}}\r\night)quad forall x,yin mathbb {R} }</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9ac96a5439c91310de854e93891d27f13b221315\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"operatorname {atan2}(y,x)={frac  pi 2}operatorname{sgn}(y)-arctan left({frac  xy}\r\night)quad forall x,yin {mathbb  R}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.505ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 49.549ex; height: 6.176ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>Siendo:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle operatorname {sgn} (y)={egin{cases}1qquad ygeq 0-1qquad y&lt;0end{cases}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/309d4b06a3c135f2be4422ad2c8f2b7c5645b6c4\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"operatorname{sgn}(y)={egin{cases}1qquad ygeq 0-1qquad y<0end{cases}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.505ex; display: inline-block; width: 24.961ex; height: 6.176ex;\"></span><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmero_complejo#cite_note-6\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">6</a></sup>â€‹</dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funci%C3%B3n_signo\" title=\"FunciÃ³n signo\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciÃ³n signo</a>.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">El argumento tiene periodicidad 2Ï€, con lo que<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle arg z=operatorname {Arg} z+2kpi }</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2137f18f187ee67b38b52ac122d16f2d50d655ac\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle arg z=operatorname {Arg} z+2kpi }\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 19.649ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>siendo<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle k}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c3c9a2c7b599b37105512c5d570edc034056dd40\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"k\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 1.211ex; height: 2.176ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>cualquier nÃºmero entero. El Ã¡ngulo Arg<span>&nbsp;</span><i>z</i><span>&nbsp;</span>es el valor principal de arg<span>&nbsp;</span><i>z</i><span>&nbsp;</span>que verifica las condiciones -Ï€ &lt; Arg<span>&nbsp;</span><i>z</i><span>&nbsp;</span>&lt;= Ï€ descritas antes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmero_complejo#cite_note-7\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">7</a></sup>â€‹</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Conjugado_de_un_n.C3.BAmero_complejo\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Conjugado_de_un_nÃºmero_complejo\">Conjugado de un nÃºmero complejo</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=N%C3%BAmero_complejo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Conjugado de un nÃºmero complejo\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Dos binomios se llaman conjugados si solo difieren en su signo central. De esta manera, el<span>&nbsp;</span><i><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjugado_(matem%C3%A1tica)\" title=\"Conjugado (matemÃ¡tica)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">conjugado</a></i><span>&nbsp;</span>de un complejo<span>&nbsp;</span><i>z</i>(denotado como<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle {ar {z}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/52dd0599595d539f7d757ec21da6c6e6ac3ad427\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{ar  {z}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 1.296ex; height: 2.009ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>o<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle z^{*},!}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1785fa3aef175b2210be42424441fd538fc29d40\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"z^{*},!\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px -0.387ex 0px 0px; display: inline-block; width: 2.532ex; height: 2.343ex;\"></span>) es un nuevo nÃºmero complejo, definido asÃ­:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle {ar {z}}=a-mathrm {i} bLongleftrightarrow z=a+mathrm {i} b}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/be3a4094d63d0abe179c50039519e6877661200d\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{ar  {z}}=a-{mathrm  {i}}bLongleftrightarrow z=a+{mathrm  {i}}b\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.505ex; display: inline-block; width: 25.617ex; height: 2.343ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Se observa que ambos difieren en el signo de la parte imaginaria. Con este nÃºmero se cumplen las propiedades:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle {overline {z+w}}={ar {z}}+{ar {w}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/920da5ee5dc0a6bde6aac4dae309e99f3a76ed1f\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"overline {z+w}={ar  {z}}+{ar  {w}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.505ex; display: inline-block; width: 14.607ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle z+{overline {z}}=2cdot {hbox{Re}}(z)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c1b78b9d7c35ab62d1c60246db1a0771dd54d5e6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"z+overline {z}=2cdot {hbox{Re}}(z)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; display: inline-block; width: 16.717ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle z-{overline {z}}=2icdot {hbox{Im}}(z)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/bdee7e2538e0cf14952d0a6ce8d1889725d0dbdf\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"z-overline {z}=2icdot {hbox{Im}}(z)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; display: inline-block; width: 17.552ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle {overline {zw}}={ar {z}}{ar {w}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/09ebb7ac2938e14771b542d90715cb5a26671f4b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"overline {zw}={ar  {z}}{ar  {w}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; display: inline-block; width: 8.926ex; height: 2.343ex;\"></span></dd></dl><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle zin mathbb {R} Longleftrightarrow {ar {z}}=z}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b38e3fe72f844e0ef9e428dc9f0979298ca8205c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"zin {mathbb  {R}}Longleftrightarrow {ar  {z}}=z\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; display: inline-block; width: 16.696ex; height: 2.176ex;\"></span></dd></dl><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle |z|^{2}=z{ar {z}}geq 0}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d0526bcc91ad1602400dc023dae1adbcd046ea56\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle |z|^{2}=z{ar {z}}geq 0}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; display: inline-block; width: 13.18ex; height: 3.343ex;\"></span></dd></dl><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle z\r\neq 0Rightarrow {frac {1}{z}}={frac {ar {z}}{|z|^{2}}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f1f55e1adb2b3b8ce8f7adf26e373c6ec57412fb\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"z\r\neq 0Rightarrow {frac  {1}{z}}={frac  {{ar  {z}}}{|z|^{2}}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -3.005ex; display: inline-block; width: 18.332ex; height: 6.343ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Esta Ãºltima fÃ³rmula es el mÃ©todo elegido para calcular el inverso de un nÃºmero complejo si viene dado en coordenadas rectangulares.</p>', 10);
INSERT INTO `cursos` (`idcurso`, `titulo`, `descripcion`, `contenido`, `idautor`) VALUES
(4, 'FRACTALES - ESPECTRO22', 'Definiciones22', '<h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Caracter.C3.ADsticas_de_un_fractal\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"CaracterÃ­sticas_de_un_fractal\">CaracterÃ­sticas de un fractal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: CaracterÃ­sticas de un fractal\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h2><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Autosimilitud\">Autosimilitud</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Autosimilitud\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">SegÃºn<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beno%C3%AEt_Mandelbrot\" title=\"BenoÃ®t Mandelbrot\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">B. Mandelbrot</a>, un objeto es<span>&nbsp;</span><b>autosimilar</b><span>&nbsp;</span>o<span>&nbsp;</span><b>autosemejante</b><span>&nbsp;</span>si sus partes tienen la misma forma o estructura que el todo, aunque pueden presentarse a diferente escala y pueden estar ligeramente deformadas.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractal#cite_note-5\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">5</a></sup>â€‹</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Los fractales pueden presentar tres tipos de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autosimilitud\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Autosimilitud\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">autosimilitud</a>:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Autosimilitud exacta</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Este es el tipo mÃ¡s restrictivo de autosimilitud: exige que el fractal parezca idÃ©ntico a diferentes escalas. A menudo la encontramos en fractales definidos por<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sistema_de_funciones_iteradas\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sistema de funciones iteradas\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">sistemas de funciones iteradas (IFS)</a>.</dd><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Cuasiautosimilitud</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: transparent;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 402px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Mandelzoom.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c6/Mandelzoom.jpg/400px-Mandelzoom.jpg\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"445\" data-file-height=\"102\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"400\" height=\"92\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><i>Cuasiautosimilitud</i><span>&nbsp;</span>en el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjunto_de_Mandelbrot\" title=\"Conjunto de Mandelbrot\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">conjunto de Mandelbrot</a>: al variar la escala obtenemos copias del conjunto con pequeÃ±as diferencias.</div></div></div></dd><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Exige que el fractal parezca aproximadamente idÃ©ntico a diferentes escalas. Los fractales de este tipo contienen copias menores y distorsionadas de sÃ­ mismos. MatemÃ¡ticamente D. Sullivan definiÃ³ el concepto de conjunto cuasiauto-similar a partir del concepto de cuasi-isometrÃ­a. Los fractales definidos por relaciones de recurrencia son normalmente de este tipo.</dd><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Autosimilitud estadÃ­stica</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Es el tipo mÃ¡s dÃ©bil de autosimilitud: se exige que el fractal tenga medidas numÃ©ricas o estadÃ­sticas que se preserven con el cambio de escala. Los fractales aleatorios son ejemplos de fractales de este tipo.</dd></dl><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Dimensi.C3.B3n_fractal_y_dimensi.C3.B3n_de_Hausdorff-Besicovitch\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"DimensiÃ³n_fractal_y_dimensiÃ³n_de_Hausdorff-Besicovitch\">DimensiÃ³n fractal y dimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: DimensiÃ³n fractal y dimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Entre los fractales podemos encontrar ejemplos como curvas que llenan todo el plano. En ese caso, la dimensiÃ³n topolÃ³gica de la curva, que es uno, no nos informa sobre la forma en que esta ocupa el espacio ambiente. De modo general, podrÃ­amos preguntarnos cÃ³mo densamente un conjunto ocupa el espacio mÃ©trico que lo contiene. Los nÃºmeros que nos informan objetivamente de este tipo de cuestiones son:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">La dimensiÃ³n fractal</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Las fÃ³rmulas que la definen tienen que ver con el recuento de las bolas necesarias para recubrir el conjunto o con el de cajas de una cuadrÃ­cula que contienen parte del conjunto, cuando las dimensiones de unas y otras tienden a cero. Podemos medir la dimensiÃ³n fractal de objetos reales: lÃ­neas de la costa (1.2), nubes, Ã¡rboles, etc, Con estas medidas podemos comparar objetos del mundo real con fractales generados por algoritmos matemÃ¡ticos.</dd><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">La dimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: transparent;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 202px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Dlasim.PNG\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Dlasim.PNG/200px-Dlasim.PNG\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"489\" data-file-height=\"490\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\"><i>Autosimilitud estadÃ­stica</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de un fractal generado por el proceso de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agregaci%C3%B3n_limitada_por_difusi%C3%B3n\" title=\"AgregaciÃ³n limitada por difusiÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">agregaciÃ³n limitada por difusiÃ³n</a>.</div></div></div></dd><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Tiene una definiciÃ³n mÃ¡s compleja que la de dimensiÃ³n fractal. Su definiciÃ³n no suele usarse para comparar conjuntos del mundo real.</dd></dl><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Definici.C3.B3n_por_algoritmos_recursivos\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"DefiniciÃ³n_por_algoritmos_recursivos\">DefiniciÃ³n por algoritmos recursivos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: DefiniciÃ³n por algoritmos recursivos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Podemos destacar tres tÃ©cnicas comunes para generar fractales:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sistema_de_funciones_iteradas\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sistema de funciones iteradas\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Sistemas de funciones iteradas</a><span>&nbsp;</span>(IFS)</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Unos conjuntos se reemplazan recursivamente por su imagen bajo un sistema de aplicaciones: el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjunto_de_Cantor\" title=\"Conjunto de Cantor\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">conjunto de Cantor</a>, la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfombra_de_Sierpinski\" title=\"Alfombra de Sierpinski\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">alfombra de Sierpinski</a>, el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tri%C3%A1ngulo_de_Sierpinski\" title=\"TriÃ¡ngulo de Sierpinski\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">triÃ¡ngulo de Sierpinski</a>, la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curva_de_Peano\" title=\"Curva de Peano\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">curva de Peano</a>, la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Curva_del_drag%C3%B3n\" title=\"Curva del dragÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">curva del dragÃ³n</a>, el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Copo_de_nieve_de_Koch\" title=\"Copo de nieve de Koch\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">copo de nieve de Koch</a><span>&nbsp;</span>o la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esponja_de_Menger\" title=\"Esponja de Menger\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Esponja de Menger</a>, son algunos ejemplos.</dd><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Fractales de algoritmos de Escape</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Definidos por una relaciÃ³n de recurrencia en cada punto del espacio (por ejemplo, el plano complejo): el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjunto_de_Mandelbrot\" title=\"Conjunto de Mandelbrot\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">conjunto de Mandelbrot</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjunto_de_Julia\" title=\"Conjunto de Julia\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">conjunto de Julia</a>, y el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal_de_Lyapunov&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Fractal de Lyapunov (aÃºn no redactado)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(165, 88, 88); background: none;\">fractal de Lyapunov</a>.</dd><dt style=\"font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">Fractales aleatorios</dt><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Generados por<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proceso_estoc%C3%A1stico\" title=\"Proceso estocÃ¡stico\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">procesos estocÃ¡sticos</a>, no deterministas: el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Movimiento_browniano\" title=\"Movimiento browniano\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">movimiento browniano</a>,el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vuelo_de_L%C3%A9vy\" title=\"Vuelo de LÃ©vy\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">vuelo de LÃ©vy</a>, los<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paisaje_fractal\" title=\"Paisaje fractal\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">paisajes fractales</a>o los Ã¡rboles brownianos. Estos Ãºltimos son producidos por procesos de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agregaci%C3%B3n_por_difusi%C3%B3n_limitada\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"AgregaciÃ³n por difusiÃ³n limitada\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">agregaciÃ³n por difusiÃ³n limitada</a>..</dd></dl><h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Aspectos_matem.C3.A1ticos\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aspectos_matemÃ¡ticos\">Aspectos matemÃ¡ticos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Aspectos matemÃ¡ticos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h2><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Intentos_de_definici.C3.B3n_rigurosa\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Intentos_de_definiciÃ³n_rigurosa\">Intentos de definiciÃ³n rigurosa</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Intentos de definiciÃ³n rigurosa\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">El concepto de fractal no dispone en el aÃ±o<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/2008\" title=\"2008\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">2008</a><span>&nbsp;</span>de una definiciÃ³n matemÃ¡tica precisa y de aceptaciÃ³n general. Intentos parciales de dar una definiciÃ³n fueron realizados por:</p><ul style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 width=%225%22 height=%2213%22%3E %3Ccircle cx=%222.5%22 cy=%229%22 r=%222.5%22 fill=%22%23222%22/%3E %3C/svg%3E&quot;); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beno%C3%AEt_Mandelbrot\" title=\"BenoÃ®t Mandelbrot\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">B. Mandelbrot</a>, que en<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/1982\" title=\"1982\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">1982</a><span>&nbsp;</span>definiÃ³ fractal como un conjunto cuya<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dimensi%C3%B3n_de_Hausdorff-Besicovitch\" title=\"DimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">dimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch</a><span>&nbsp;</span>es estrictamente mayor que su<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dimensi%C3%B3n_topol%C3%B3gica\" title=\"DimensiÃ³n topolÃ³gica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">dimensiÃ³n topolÃ³gica</a>. Ã‰l mismo reconociÃ³ que su definiciÃ³n no era lo suficientemente general.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\">D. Sullivan, que definiÃ³ matemÃ¡ticamente una de las categorÃ­as de fractales con su definiciÃ³n de conjunto cuasiautosimilar que hacÃ­a uso del concepto de cuasi-isometrÃ­a.</li></ul><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Dimensi.C3.B3n_fractal\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"DimensiÃ³n_fractal\">DimensiÃ³n fractal</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: DimensiÃ³n fractal\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"noprint AP rellink\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.32px;\">ArtÃ­culo principal:</span><span>&nbsp;</span><i style=\"font-style: normal;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dimensi%C3%B3n_fractal\" title=\"DimensiÃ³n fractal\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">DimensiÃ³n fractal</a></i></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Puede definirse en tÃ©rminos del mÃ­nimo nÃºmero<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle N(epsilon )}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e8d77d8d8945a2bad6f11a2974db2febe676eeaf\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"N(epsilon )\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 4.817ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>de bolas de radio<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle epsilon }</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c3837cad72483d97bcdde49c85d3b7b859fb3fd2\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"epsilon \" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 0.944ex; height: 1.676ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>necesarias para recubrir el conjunto, como el lÃ­mite:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle D_{F}=lim _{epsilon 	o 0}{ln N(epsilon ) over ln(1/epsilon )}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2e5fa436414f4bf6b38218492c1e213d72b9c4d4\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"D_{F}=lim _{{epsilon 	o 0}}{ln N(epsilon ) over ln(1/epsilon )}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.671ex; display: inline-block; width: 18.082ex; height: 6.509ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">O en funciÃ³n del recuento del nÃºmero de cajas<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle N_{n}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e1726319d75a0531be1b14f4f9a0c3bee00b786a\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"N_{n}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 3.085ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>de una cuadrÃ­cula de anchura<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle 1/2^{n}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/afcca0eda567be34036ddbb204671dc6aee9975f\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"1/2^{n}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 4.706ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>que intersecan al conjunto:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle D_{F}=lim _{n	o infty }{ln N_{n} over ln(2^{n})}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d4252858429e95db03b884de3c59aed12e825f34\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"D_{F}=lim _{{n	o infty }}{ln N_{n} over ln(2^{n})}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.671ex; display: inline-block; width: 18.111ex; height: 6.176ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Se demuestra que ambas definiciones son equivalentes, y que son invariantes bajo isometrÃ­as.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractal#cite_note-6\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">6</a></sup>â€‹</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Dimensi.C3.B3n_de_Hausdorff-Besicovitch\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"DimensiÃ³n_de_Hausdorff-Besicovitch\">DimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: DimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">De una definiciÃ³n mÃ¡s compleja, la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dimensi%C3%B3n#dimensi%C3%B3n_de_Hausdorff-Besicovitch\" title=\"DimensiÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">dimensiÃ³n de Hausdorff-Besicovitch</a><span>&nbsp;</span>nos proporciona un nÃºmero<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle D_{H}(A)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/69bff305ccb96dd15f3cb07f31a0aecd10f6005b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"D_{H}(A)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 7.168ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span>, tambiÃ©n invariante bajo isometrÃ­as, cuya relaciÃ³n con la dimensiÃ³n fractal<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle D_{F}(A)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/dde09308bb631439e5ecfba210bb05c418376b5d\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"D_{F}(A)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 6.94ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>es la siguiente:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle 0leq D_{H}(A)leq D_{F}(A)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/011a4650f9d9d80046837338616a20ddba0384a6\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"0leq D_{H}(A)leq D_{F}(A)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; display: inline-block; width: 21.467ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Esto permite distinguir en algunos casos entre conjuntos con la misma dimensiÃ³n fractal.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Dimensi.C3.B3n_de_fractales_producidos_por_un_IFS\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"DimensiÃ³n_de_fractales_producidos_por_un_IFS\">DimensiÃ³n de fractales producidos por un IFS</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: DimensiÃ³n de fractales producidos por un IFS\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sistema_iterativo_de_funciones\" title=\"Sistema iterativo de funciones\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">sistema iterativo de funciones</a><span>&nbsp;</span>(IFS) es un conjunto de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contracci%C3%B3n_(espacio_m%C3%A9trico)\" title=\"ContracciÃ³n (espacio mÃ©trico)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciones contractivas</a><span>&nbsp;</span>definidas sobre un subconjunto de<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle mathbb {R} ^{n}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c510b63578322050121fe966f2e5770bea43308d\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"mathbb {R} ^{n}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 2.897ex; height: 2.343ex;\"></span>. Cuando no hay solapamiento entre las imÃ¡genes de cada funciÃ³n, se demuestra que<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle D_{F}=D_{H}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/3cfb9f092ae62d9593f449bf51ef9382c747e673\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"D_{F}=D_{H}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 10.102ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>y que ambas pueden calcularse como soluciÃ³n de la ecuaciÃ³n:</p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle c_{1}^{D}+c_{2}^{D}+dots +c_{k}^{D}=1}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/c8fe138e55c02c9f4c4c74eff6bdd950ceb36de0\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"c_{1}^{D}+c_{2}^{D}+dots +c_{k}^{D}=1\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -1.005ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 23.305ex; height: 3.176ex;\"></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">donde c<sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\">i</sub><span>&nbsp;</span>designa el factor de contracciÃ³n de cada aplicaciÃ³n contractiva del IFS.</p><h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aplicaciones\">Aplicaciones</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Aplicaciones\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Se han utilizado tÃ©cnicas de fractales en la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compresi%C3%B3n_de_datos\" title=\"CompresiÃ³n de datos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">compresiÃ³n de datos</a><span>&nbsp;</span>y en diversas disciplinas cientÃ­ficas.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Compresi.C3.B3n_de_im.C3.A1genes\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"CompresiÃ³n_de_imÃ¡genes\">CompresiÃ³n de imÃ¡genes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=18\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: CompresiÃ³n de imÃ¡genes\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"floatleft\" style=\"float: left; clear: left; position: relative; margin: 0px 0.5em 0.5em 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Fractal_fern_explained.png\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"Fractal fern explained.png\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4b/Fractal_fern_explained.png/150px-Fractal_fern_explained.png\" data-file-width=\"333\" data-file-height=\"465\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: middle;\" width=\"150\" height=\"209\"></a></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Comprimir la imagen de un objeto autosemejante como el helecho de la figura no es difÃ­cil: haciendo uso del<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sistema_de_funciones_iteradas#El_problema_inverso:_Teorema_del_collage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sistema de funciones iteradas\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">teorema del collage</a>, debemos encontrar un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sistema_de_funciones_iteradas\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sistema de funciones iteradas\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">IFS</a>, conjunto de transformaciones que lleva la figura completa (en negro) en cada una de sus partes autosemejantes (rojo, azul celeste y azul marino). La informaciÃ³n sobre la imagen quedarÃ¡ codificada en el IFS, y la aplicaciÃ³n reiterada de dichas transformaciones permite obtener la imagen procesada en cuestiÃ³n.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Pero el enfoque anterior plantea problemas con muchas imÃ¡genes reales: no esperamos, por ejemplo, que la imagen de un gato presente pequeÃ±os gatitos distorsionados sobre sÃ­ mismo. Para solventarlo, en 1989 Arnaud Jacquin creÃ³ el esquema de<span>&nbsp;</span><i>sistemas de funciones iteradas particionadas</i>: en Ã©l se subdivide la imagen mediante una<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partici%C3%B3n_(matem%C3%A1tica)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ParticiÃ³n (matemÃ¡tica)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">particiÃ³n</a><span>&nbsp;</span>y para cada regiÃ³n resultante se busca otra regiÃ³n similar a la primera bajo las transformaciones apropiadas.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fractal#cite_note-7\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">7</a></sup>â€‹</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">El esquema resultante es un sistema de compresiÃ³n con pÃ©rdidas, de tiempo asimÃ©trico. Lamentablemente aÃºn se tarda mucho en encontrar las transformaciones que definen la imagen. No obstante, una vez encontradas, la descodificaciÃ³n es muy rÃ¡pida. La compresiÃ³n, aunque dependa de muchos factores, suele ser equiparable a la compresiÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/JPEG\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"JPEG\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">JPEG</a>, con lo cual el factor tiempo resulta determinante para decantarse por uno u otro sistema.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Modelado_de_formas_naturales\">Modelado de formas naturales</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=19\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Modelado de formas naturales\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 202px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Fractal471763.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Fractal471763.jpg/200px-Fractal471763.jpg\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"800\" data-file-height=\"600\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"200\" height=\"150\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\">FracciÃ³n de un fractal Mandelbrot.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Las formas fractales, las formas en la que las partes se asemejan al todo, estÃ¡n presentes en la materia biolÃ³gica, junto con las simetrÃ­as (las formas bÃ¡sicas que solo necesitan la mitad de informaciÃ³n genÃ©tica) y las espirales (las formas de crecimiento y desarrollo de la forma bÃ¡sica hacia la ocupaciÃ³n de un mayor espacio), como las formas mÃ¡s sofisticadas en el desarrollo evolutivo de la materia biolÃ³gica en cuanto que se presentan en procesos en los que se producen saltos cualitativos en las formas biolÃ³gicas, es decir posibilitan catÃ¡strofes (hechos extraordinarios) que dan lugar a nuevas realidades mÃ¡s complejas, como las hojas que presentan una morfologÃ­a similar a la pequeÃ±a rama de la que forman parte que, a su vez, presentan una forma similar a la rama, que a su vez es similar a la forma del Ã¡rbol, y sin embargo cualitativamente no es lo mismo una hoja (forma biolÃ³gica simple), que una rama o un Ã¡rbol (forma biolÃ³gica compleja).</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Sistemas_din.C3.A1micos\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sistemas_dinÃ¡micos\">Sistemas dinÃ¡micos</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Sistemas dinÃ¡micos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 202px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:LorenzAttractor.png\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/LorenzAttractor.png/200px-LorenzAttractor.png\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"378\" data-file-height=\"199\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"200\" height=\"105\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\">Un atractor extraÃ±o: el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atractor_de_Lorenz\" title=\"Atractor de Lorenz\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">atractor de Lorenz</a>.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Pero ademÃ¡s las formas fractales no solo se presentan en las formas espaciales de los objetos sino que se observan en la propia dinÃ¡mica evolutiva de los sistemas complejos (ver<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teor%C3%ADa_del_caos\" title=\"TeorÃ­a del caos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">teorÃ­a del caos</a>). DinÃ¡mica que consta de ciclos (en los que partiendo de una realidad establecida simple acaban en la creaciÃ³n de una nueva realidad mÃ¡s compleja) que a su vez forman parte de ciclos mÃ¡s complejos los cuales forman parte del desarrollo de la dinÃ¡mica de otro gran ciclo. Las evoluciones dinÃ¡micas de todos estos ciclos presentan las similitudes propias de los sistemas caÃ³ticos.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"En_manifestaciones_art.C3.ADsticas\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"En_manifestaciones_artÃ­sticas\">En manifestaciones artÃ­sticas</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;section=21\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: En manifestaciones artÃ­sticas\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 202px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Sandstorm.png\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Sandstorm.png/200px-Sandstorm.png\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"1440\" data-file-height=\"900\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"200\" height=\"125\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\">Imagen generada con el programa Apophysis.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">La mÃºsica puede contener formas fractales. Algunas obras clÃ¡sicas de Beethoven, Bach y Mozart son ejemplos representativos segÃºn revelÃ³ un estudio.<sup style=\"line-height: 1em;\">[<i><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verificabilidad\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verificabilidad\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">cita&nbsp;requerida</a></i>]</sup><span>&nbsp;</span>El mÃ©todo que siguieron estos compositores, ya sea de manera intencionada o no, para integrar fractales y matemÃ¡ticas era mediante una analogÃ­a entre una dimensiÃ³n fractal y el nÃºmero y la disposiciÃ³n de las diferentes notas de una obra o pieza.<sup style=\"line-height: 1em;\">[<i><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verificabilidad\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verificabilidad\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">cita&nbsp;requerida</a></i>]</sup></p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Se usan tanto en la composiciÃ³n armÃ³nica y rÃ­tmica de una melodÃ­a como en la sÃ­ntesis de sonidos. Esto se debe al uso de lo que en composiciÃ³n se llaman \"micromodos\", o pequeÃ±os grupos de tres notas, a partir de los cuales uno puede trabajarlos de manera horizontal (<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mel%C3%B3dica\" title=\"MelÃ³dica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">melÃ³dica</a>), o vertical (<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arm%C3%B3nica\" title=\"ArmÃ³nica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">armÃ³nica</a>). A su vez, el ritmo puede ser trabajado en sucesiones temporales especÃ­ficas, que son determinadas por sucesiones de fractales.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Por otra parte, las<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Litograf%C3%ADas\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"LitografÃ­as\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">litografÃ­as</a><span>&nbsp;</span>del artista holandÃ©s<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maurits_Cornelis_Escher\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maurits Cornelis Escher\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Maurits Cornelis Escher</a><span>&nbsp;</span>(1898-1972) desarrollaron con frecuencia estructuras matemÃ¡ticas complejas y avanzadas.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Con programas informÃ¡ticos como<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apophysis\" title=\"Apophysis\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Apophysis</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sterling_(programa)\" title=\"Sterling (programa)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Sterling</a><span>&nbsp;</span>o<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Ultra_Fractal&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ultra Fractal (aÃºn no redactado)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(165, 88, 88); background: none;\">Ultra Fractal</a><span>&nbsp;</span>se pueden hacer imÃ¡genes con tÃ©cnicas diversas; cambiando parÃ¡metros, geometrÃ­a de triÃ¡ngulos o con transformaciones aleatorias.</p><br>', 10);
INSERT INTO `cursos` (`idcurso`, `titulo`, `descripcion`, `contenido`, `idautor`) VALUES
(5, 'INTEGRALES', 'Metodos', '<h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Definiciones_formales\">Definiciones formales</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Integraci%C3%B3n&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Definiciones formales\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Hay muchas maneras de definir formalmente una integral, no todas equivalentes. Se establecen diferencias para poder abordar casos especiales que no pueden ser integrables con otras definiciones, pero tambiÃ©n en ocasiones por razones pedagÃ³gicas. Las definiciones mÃ¡s utilizadas de la integral son las integrales de Riemann y las integrales de Lebesgue.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Integral_de_Riemann\">Integral de Riemann</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Integraci%C3%B3n&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Integral de Riemann\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"noprint AP rellink\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.32px;\">ArtÃ­culo principal:</span><span>&nbsp;</span><i style=\"font-style: normal;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral_de_Riemann\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Integral de Riemann\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Integral de Riemann</a></i></div><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 222px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Integral_Riemann_sum.png\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Integral_Riemann_sum.png/220px-Integral_Riemann_sum.png\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"1260\" data-file-height=\"1260\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"220\" height=\"220\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\">Integral con el planteamiento de Riemann hace una suma basada en una<span>&nbsp;</span><i>particiÃ³n etiquetada</i>, con posiciones de muestreo y anchuras irregulares (el mÃ¡ximo en rojo). El verdadero valor es 3,76; la estimaciÃ³n obtenida es 3,648.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">La integral de Riemann se define en tÃ©rminos de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suma_de_Riemann\" title=\"Suma de Riemann\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">sumas de Riemann</a><span>&nbsp;</span>de funciones respecto de<span>&nbsp;</span><i>particiones etiquetadas</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de un intervalo. Sea [<i>a</i>,<i>b</i>] un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intervalo_(matem%C3%A1ticas)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Intervalo (matemÃ¡ticas)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">intervalo</a><span>&nbsp;</span>cerrado de la recta real; entonces una<span>&nbsp;</span><i>particiÃ³n etiquetada</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de [<i>a</i>,<i>b</i>] es una secuencia finita</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle a=x_{0}leq t_{1}leq x_{1}leq t_{2}leq x_{2}leq cdots leq x_{n-1}leq t_{n}leq x_{n}=b.,!}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7a95dc34e72c3da728c59d5f83e148f3e57f100b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"a=x_{0}leq t_{1}leq x_{1}leq t_{2}leq x_{2}leq cdots leq x_{{n-1}}leq t_{n}leq x_{n}=b.,!\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; display: inline-block; margin-right: -0.387ex; width: 57.164ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>y denotamos la particiÃ³n como<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle {mathit {P}}={x_{i}|i=0,1,...,n},!}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5e10da5aa504922409bf433e0f719180bb6f95fe\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{mathit  {P}}={x_{i}|i=0,1,...,n},!\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; display: inline-block; margin-right: -0.387ex; width: 23.987ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><div class=\"thumb tleft\" style=\"float: left; clear: left; margin: 0.5em 1.4em 1.3em 0px; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 252px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Riemann_sum_convergence.png\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/Riemann_sum_convergence.png/250px-Riemann_sum_convergence.png\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"1260\" data-file-height=\"1260\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\">Convergencia de sumatorios de Riemann a medida en que se parten los intervalos, cuando se muestrea a<span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 129, 205);\">â– </span>&nbsp;la derecha,<span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(188, 30, 71);\">â– </span>&nbsp;el mÃ­nimo,<span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 146, 70);\">â– </span>&nbsp;el mÃ¡ximo, o<span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(254, 194, 0);\">â– </span>&nbsp;la izquierda.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Esto divide al intervalo [<i>a</i>,<i>b</i>] en<span>&nbsp;</span><i>n</i>subintervalos [<i>x</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i>âˆ’1</sub>,<span>&nbsp;</span><i>x</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub>], cada uno de los cuales es \"etiquetado\" con un punto especificado<span>&nbsp;</span><i>t</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub><span>&nbsp;</span>de; [<i>x</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i>âˆ’1</sub>,<span>&nbsp;</span><i>x</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub>]. Sea Î”<sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub>&nbsp;=<span>&nbsp;</span><i>x</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub>âˆ’<i>x</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i>âˆ’1</sub><span>&nbsp;</span>la anchura del subintervalo<span>&nbsp;</span><i>i</i>; el<span>&nbsp;</span><i>paso</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de esta particiÃ³n etiquetada es el ancho del subintervalo mÃ¡s grande obtenido por la particiÃ³n, max<sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i>=1â€¦<i>n</i></sub>&nbsp;Î”<sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub>. Un<span>&nbsp;</span><i>sumatorio de Riemann</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de una funciÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i><span>&nbsp;</span>respecto de esta particiÃ³n etiquetada se define como</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle sum _{i=1}^{n}f(t_{i})Delta _{i};}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f988bf16d04d532a77e978ed1d82addfb9ab761c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}f(t_{i})Delta _{i};\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -3.005ex; display: inline-block; width: 11.852ex; height: 6.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">AsÃ­ cada tÃ©rmino del sumatorio es el Ã¡rea del rectÃ¡ngulo con altura igual al valor de la funciÃ³n en el punto especificado del subintervalo dado, y de la misma anchura que la anchura del subintervalo. La<span>&nbsp;</span><i>integral de Riemann</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de una funciÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i><span>&nbsp;</span>sobre el intervalo [<i>a</i>,<i>b</i>] es igual a<span>&nbsp;</span><i>S</i><span>&nbsp;</span>si:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\">Para todo Îµ&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;0 existe Î´&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;0 tal que, para cualquier particiÃ³n etiquetada [<i>a</i>,<i>b</i>] con paso mÃ¡s pequeÃ±o que Î´, se tiene<dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle left|S-sum _{i=1}^{n}f(t_{i})Delta _{i}\r\night|&lt;varepsilon }</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b8b89f48e57331912830f5c431eaae344bb41b5e\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"left|S-sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}f(t_{i})Delta _{i}\r\night|<varepsilon \" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -3.005ex; display: inline-block; width: 21.02ex; height: 7.176ex;\"></span>, donde<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle S=int _{a}^{b}f=lim _{|{Delta _{i}}|	o 0}sum _{i=1}^{n}f(t_{i})Delta _{i}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5a9c902b384de100f021a6f111d03a983d2081bf\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"S=int _{{a}}^{{b}}f=lim _{{|{Delta _{i}}|	o 0}}sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}f(t_{i})Delta _{i}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -3.005ex; display: inline-block; width: 30.458ex; height: 7.009ex;\"></span></dd></dl></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Cuando las etiquetas escogidas dan el mÃ¡ximo (o mÃ­nimo) valor de cada intervalo, el sumatorio de Riemann pasa a ser un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral_de_Darboux\" title=\"Integral de Darboux\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">sumatorio de Darboux</a><span>&nbsp;</span>superior (o inferior), lo que sugiere la estrecha conexiÃ³n que hay entre la integral de Riemann y la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral_de_Darboux\" title=\"Integral de Darboux\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">integral de Darboux</a>.</p><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Integral_de_Darboux\">Integral de Darboux</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Integraci%C3%B3n&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Integral de Darboux\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"noprint AP rellink\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.32px;\">ArtÃ­culo principal:</span><span>&nbsp;</span><i style=\"font-style: normal;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral_de_Darboux\" title=\"Integral de Darboux\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Integral de Darboux</a></i></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">La Integral de Darboux se define en tÃ©rminos de sumas de los siguientes tipos:</p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle L({mathit {f}},P)=sum _{i}^{n}m_{i}(x_{i}-x_{i-1}),qquad U({mathit {f}},P)=sum _{i}^{n}M_{i}(x_{i}-x_{i-1})}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7f99957096d46ff865223d6a6469987a862019c2\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"L({mathit  {f}},P)=sum _{{i}}^{{n}}m_{i}(x_{i}-x_{{i-1}}),qquad U({mathit  {f}},P)=sum _{{i}}^{{n}}M_{i}(x_{i}-x_{{i-1}})\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -3.005ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 61.243ex; height: 6.843ex;\"></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Llamadas suma inferior y superior respectivamente, donde:</p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle M_{i}=sup{f(x)|xin [x_{i-1},x_{i}]},qquad m_{i}=inf{f(x)|xin [x_{i-1},x_{i}]}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/95323cbbe7a736f7a7cfc35bd1854746e178366c\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"M_{i}=sup{f(x)|xin [x_{{i-1}},x_{i}]},qquad m_{i}=inf{f(x)|xin [x_{{i-1}},x_{i}]}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 64.415ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">son las alturas de los rectÃ¡ngulos, y<span>&nbsp;</span><i>x<sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\">i</sub>-x<sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\">i-1</sub></i><span>&nbsp;</span>la longitud de la base de los rectÃ¡ngulos. La integral de Darboux estÃ¡ definida como el Ãºnico nÃºmero acotado entre las sumas inferior y superior, es decir,</p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle L(f,P)leq int _{a}^{b}fleq U(f,P)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e28fca31fb03d8a1ad81ffef9d64ae782bb577c3\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"L(f,P)leq int _{{a}}^{{b}}fleq U(f,P)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 26.364ex; height: 6.343ex;\"></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">La interpretaciÃ³n geomÃ©trica de la integral de Darboux serÃ­a el cÃ¡lculo del Ã¡rea de la regiÃ³n en [<i>a,b</i>] por el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/M%C3%A9todo_exhaustivo\" title=\"MÃ©todo exhaustivo\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">MÃ©todo exhaustivo</a>. La<span>&nbsp;</span><i>integral de Darboux</i><span>&nbsp;</span>de una funciÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i><span>&nbsp;</span>en [<i>a,b</i>] existe<span>&nbsp;</span><i>si y solo si</i></p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle sup leftlbrace L(f,P)\r\night\r\nbrace =inf leftlbrace U(f,P)\r\night\r\nbrace }</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a55227eab733d6fffb168355f7091e4021e64bac\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"sup leftlbrace L(f,P)\r\night\r\nbrace =inf leftlbrace U(f,P)\r\night\r\nbrace \" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 29.775ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Del Teorema de CaracterizaciÃ³n que dice que si<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i><span>&nbsp;</span>es integrable en [<i>a,b</i>] entonces âˆ€Îµ&gt;0 âˆƒ<span>&nbsp;</span><i>P</i><span>&nbsp;</span>particiÃ³n de [<i>a,b</i>]&nbsp;: 0â‰¤U(<i>f,P</i>)-L(<i>f,P</i>)â‰¤Îµ, evidencia la equivalencia entre las definiciones de Integral de Riemman e Integral de Darboux pues se sigue que<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integraci%C3%B3n#cite_note-7\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">7</a></sup>â€‹</p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle int _{a}^{b}f-sum _{i=1}^{n}f(t_{i})Delta _{i}leq U(f,P)-L(f,P)leq varepsilon }</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f809dda46f16781ff659257ed3a940c7786e5014\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"int _{{a}}^{{b}}f-sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}f(t_{i})Delta _{i}leq U(f,P)-L(f,P)leq varepsilon \" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -3.005ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 44.333ex; height: 7.009ex;\"></span>.</p></blockquote><h3 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: bold; margin: 0.3em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding-top: 0.5em; padding-bottom: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.6; font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Integral_de_Lebesgue\">Integral de Lebesgue</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Integraci%C3%B3n&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: Integral de Lebesgue\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h3><div class=\"noprint AP rellink\" style=\"font-style: italic; padding-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.32px;\">ArtÃ­culo principal:</span><span>&nbsp;</span><i style=\"font-style: normal;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral_de_Lebesgue\" title=\"Integral de Lebesgue\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Integral de Lebesgue</a></i></div><div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 252px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:RandLintegrals.png\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/RandLintegrals.png/250px-RandLintegrals.png\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"569\" data-file-height=\"349\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"250\" height=\"153\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\">IntegraciÃ³n de Riemann-Darboux (azul) e integraciÃ³n de Lebesgue (rojo).</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">La integral de Riemann no estÃ¡ definida para un ancho abanico de funciones y situaciones de importancia prÃ¡ctica (y de interÃ©s teÃ³rico). Por ejemplo, la integral de Riemann puede integrar fÃ¡cilmente la densidad para obtener la masa de una viga de acero, pero no se puede adaptar a una bola de acero que se apoya encima. Esto motiva la creaciÃ³n de otras definiciones, bajo las cuales se puede integrar un surtido mÃ¡s amplio de funciones.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integraci%C3%B3n#cite_note-8\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">8</a></sup>â€‹ La integral de Lebesgue, en particular, logra una gran flexibilidad a base de centrar la atenciÃ³n en los pesos de la suma ponderada.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">AsÃ­, la definiciÃ³n de la integral de Lebesgue empieza con una<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medida_(matem%C3%A1ticas)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Medida (matemÃ¡ticas)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">medida</a>, Î¼. En el caso mÃ¡s sencillo, la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medida_de_Lebesgue\" title=\"Medida de Lebesgue\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">medida de Lebesgue</a><span>&nbsp;</span>Î¼(<i>A</i>) de un intervalo<span>&nbsp;</span><i>A</i><span>&nbsp;</span>= [<i>a</i>,<span>&nbsp;</span><i>b</i>] es su ancho,<span>&nbsp;</span><i>b</i><span>&nbsp;</span>âˆ’<span>&nbsp;</span><i>a</i>, asÃ­ la integral de Lebesgue coincide con la integral de Riemann cuando existen ambas. En casos mÃ¡s complicados, los conjuntos a medir pueden estar altamente fragmentados, sin continuidad y sin ningÃºn parecido a intervalos.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Para explotar esta flexibilidad, la integral de Lebesgue invierte el enfoque de la suma ponderada. Como expresa Folland:<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integraci%C3%B3n#cite_note-9\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">9</a></sup>â€‹ \"Para calcular la integral de Riemann de<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i>, se particiona el dominio [<i>a</i>,<span>&nbsp;</span><i>b</i>] en subintervalos\", mientras que en la integral de Lebesgue, \"de hecho lo que se estÃ¡ particionando es el recorrido de<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i>\".</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Un enfoque habitual define primero la integral de la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funci%C3%B3n_indicatriz\" title=\"FunciÃ³n indicatriz\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciÃ³n caracterÃ­stica</a><span>&nbsp;</span>de un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teor%C3%ADa_de_la_medida\" title=\"TeorÃ­a de la medida\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">conjunto medible</a><span>&nbsp;</span><i>A</i><span>&nbsp;</span>por:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle int 1_{A}dmu =mu (A)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/de816199e0d266a5a065862563511b80aa31bf08\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"int 1_{A}dmu =mu (A)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.338ex; display: inline-block; width: 15.878ex; height: 5.676ex;\"></span>.</dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Esto se extiende por linealidad a las<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Funciones_escalonadas&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Funciones escalonadas (aÃºn no redactado)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(165, 88, 88); background: none;\">funciones escalonadas</a><span>&nbsp;</span>simples, que solo tienen un nÃºmero finito<span>&nbsp;</span><i>n</i>, de valores diferentes no negativos:</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle {egin{aligned}int s,dmu &amp;{}=int left(sum _{i=1}^{n}a_{i}1_{A_{i}}\r\night)dmu &amp;{}=sum _{i=1}^{n}a_{i}int 1_{A_{i}},dmu &amp;{}=sum _{i=1}^{n}a_{i},mu (A_{i})end{aligned}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a5973d40b2bc4e5b75f87b4367f08149a5c2cb59\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{egin{aligned}int s,dmu &amp;{}=int left(sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}a_{i}1_{{A_{i}}}\r\night)dmu &amp;{}=sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}a_{i}int 1_{{A_{i}}},dmu &amp;{}=sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}a_{i},mu (A_{i})end{aligned}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -10.338ex; display: inline-block; width: 28.816ex; height: 21.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">(donde la imagen de<span>&nbsp;</span><i>A</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub><span>&nbsp;</span>al aplicarle la funciÃ³n escalonada<span>&nbsp;</span><i>s</i><span>&nbsp;</span>es el valor constante<span>&nbsp;</span><i>a</i><sub style=\"line-height: 1em;\"><i>i</i></sub>). AsÃ­, si<span>&nbsp;</span><i>E</i><span>&nbsp;</span>es un conjunto medible, se define</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle int _{E}s,dmu =sum _{i=1}^{n}a_{i},mu (A_{i}cap E).}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/181170cfd1731e7ac28de670db3490af8a617ee9\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"int _{E}s,dmu =sum _{{i=1}}^{{n}}a_{i},mu (A_{i}cap E).\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -3.005ex; display: inline-block; width: 27.278ex; height: 6.843ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Entonces, para cualquier<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funci%C3%B3n_medible\" title=\"FunciÃ³n medible\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciÃ³n medible</a><span>&nbsp;</span>no negativa<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i><span>&nbsp;</span>se define</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle int _{E}f,dmu =sup left{int _{E}s,dmu ,colon 0leq sleq f{	ext{ y }}s{	ext{es una funcion escalonada}}\r\night};}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4287fe161100e66ab9db5e847a5f93d9b7249f58\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle int _{E}f,dmu =sup left{int _{E}s,dmu ,colon 0leq sleq f{	ext{ y }}s{	ext{es una funcion escalonada}}\r\night};}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.505ex; display: inline-block; width: 66.581ex; height: 6.176ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Es decir, se establece que la integral de<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i><span>&nbsp;</span>es el<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supremo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Supremo\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">supremo</a><span>&nbsp;</span>de todas las integrales de funciones escalonadas que son mÃ¡s pequeÃ±as o iguales que<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i>. Una funciÃ³n medible cualquiera<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i>, se separa entre sus valores positivos y negativos a base de definir</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle {egin{aligned}f^{+}(x)&amp;{}={egin{cases}f(x),&amp;{	ext{si }}f(x)&gt;0ï¿½,&amp;{	ext{de otro modo}}end{cases}}f^{-}(x)&amp;{}={egin{cases}-f(x),&amp;{	ext{si }}f(x)&lt;0ï¿½,&amp;{	ext{de otro modo}}end{cases}}end{aligned}}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f5e2216cb8a79312f2694c7d9de117232836808b\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{egin{aligned}f^{+}(x)&amp;{}={egin{cases}f(x),&amp;{	ext{si }}f(x)>0ï¿½,&amp;{	ext{de otro modo}}end{cases}}f^{-}(x)&amp;{}={egin{cases}-f(x),&amp;{	ext{si }}f(x)<0ï¿½,&amp;{	ext{de otro modo}}end{cases}}end{aligned}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -5.671ex; display: inline-block; width: 34.691ex; height: 12.509ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Finalmente,<span>&nbsp;</span><i>f</i><span>&nbsp;</span>es Lebesgue integrable si</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle int _{E}|f|,dmu &lt;infty ,,!}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/e8dffd04dc27c8da6c1a62d03c3e79aa9d97c037\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"int _{E}|f|,dmu <infty ,,!\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.338ex; display: inline-block; margin-right: -0.387ex; width: 15.201ex; height: 5.676ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">y entonces se define la integral por</p><dl style=\"margin-top: 0.2em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><dd style=\"margin-left: 1.6em; margin-bottom: 0.1em; margin-right: 0px;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle int _{E}f,dmu =int _{E}f^{+},dmu -int _{E}f^{-},dmu .,!}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/805b2868d1d292d1730e2e263427f85aec90ae42\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"int _{E}f,dmu =int _{E}f^{+},dmu -int _{E}f^{-},dmu .,!\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.338ex; display: inline-block; margin-right: -0.387ex; width: 32.43ex; height: 5.676ex;\"></span></dd></dl><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Cuando el espacio mÃ©trico en el que estÃ¡n definidas las funciones es tambiÃ©n un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Espacio_topol%C3%B3gico\" title=\"Espacio topolÃ³gico\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">espacio topolÃ³gico</a><span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compacidad_local\" title=\"Compacidad local\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">localmente compacto</a>(como es el caso de los nÃºmeros reales<span>&nbsp;</span><b>R</b>), las medidas compatibles con la topologÃ­a en un sentido adecuado (<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Medida_de_Radon&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Medida de Radon (aÃºn no redactado)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(165, 88, 88); background: none;\">medidas de Radon</a>, de las cuales es un ejemplo la medida de Lebesgue) una integral respecto de ellas se puede definir de otra manera, se empieza a partir de las integrales de las<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funciones_continuas\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Funciones continuas\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciones continuas</a><span>&nbsp;</span>con<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soporte_(matem%C3%A1ticas)#soporte_compacto\" title=\"Soporte (matemÃ¡ticas)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">soporte compacto</a>. De forma mÃ¡s precisa, las funciones compactamente soportadas forman un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Espacio_vectorial\" title=\"Espacio vectorial\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">espacio vectorial</a><span>&nbsp;</span>que comporta una<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Espacio_topol%C3%B3gico\" title=\"Espacio topolÃ³gico\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">topologÃ­a</a><span>&nbsp;</span>natural, y se puede definir una medida (Radon) como<span>&nbsp;</span><i>cualquier</i><span>&nbsp;</span>funcional<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aplicaci%C3%B3n_lineal\" title=\"AplicaciÃ³n lineal\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">lineal</a><span>&nbsp;</span>continuo de este espacio; entonces el valor de una medida en una funciÃ³n compactamente soportada, es tambiÃ©n, por definiciÃ³n, la integral de la funciÃ³n. Entonces se continÃºa expandiendo la medida (la integral) a funciones mÃ¡s generales por continuidad, y se define la medida de un conjunto como la integral de su funciÃ³n caracterÃ­stica.<br></p><br>', 10);
INSERT INTO `cursos` (`idcurso`, `titulo`, `descripcion`, `contenido`, `idautor`) VALUES
(6, 'Suma', 'OperaciÃ³n matemÃ¡tica ', '<div class=\"thumb tright\" style=\"clear: right; float: right; margin: 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; overflow: hidden; width: 122px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Addition01.svg\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"operaciÃ³n matemÃ¡tica suma 3 + 2 = 5\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/Addition01.svg/120px-Addition01.svg.png\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"185\" data-file-height=\"336\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"120\" height=\"218\" id=\"img_1555867235675\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px none; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px;\">3 + 2 = 5</div></div></div><br><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\">La suma es una operaciÃ³n bÃ¡sica de la aritmÃ©tica de los nÃºmeros naturales, enteros, racionales, reales y complejos; por su naturalidad, que se representa con el signo \"+\", el cual se combina con facilidad de facilidad matemÃ¡tica de composiciÃ³n en la que consiste en combinar o aÃ±adir dos nÃºmeros o mÃ¡s para obtener una cantidad final o total. La adiciÃ³n tambiÃ©n ilustra el proceso de juntar dos colecciones de objetos con el fin de obtener una sola colecciÃ³n. Por otro lado, la acciÃ³n repetitiva de sumar&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uno\" title=\"Uno\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">uno</a>&nbsp;es la forma mÃ¡s bÃ¡sica de contar.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\">En tÃ©rminos mÃ¡s formales, la suma es una operaciÃ³n&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aritm%C3%A9tica\" title=\"AritmÃ©tica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">aritmÃ©tica</a>&nbsp;definida sobre conjuntos de nÃºmeros (<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_naturales\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros naturales\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">naturales</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_enteros\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros enteros\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">enteros</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_racionales\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros racionales\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">racionales</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_reales\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros reales\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">reales</a>&nbsp;y&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_complejos\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros complejos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">complejos</a>), y tambiÃ©n sobre estructuras asociadas a ellos, como&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Espacio_vectorial\" title=\"Espacio vectorial\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">espacios vectoriales</a>&nbsp;con vectores cuyas componentes sean estos nÃºmeros o&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funci%C3%B3n_matem%C3%A1tica\" title=\"FunciÃ³n matemÃ¡tica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciones</a>&nbsp;que tengan su&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conjunto_imagen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Conjunto imagen\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">imagen</a>&nbsp;en ellos. TambiÃ©n se suman matrices.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-align: justify;\">En el&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%81lgebra_abstracta\" title=\"Ãlgebra abstracta\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Ã¡lgebra moderna</a>&nbsp;se utiliza el nombre&nbsp;suma&nbsp;y su sÃ­mbolo \"+\" para representar la&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operaci%C3%B3n_matem%C3%A1tica\" title=\"OperaciÃ³n matemÃ¡tica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">operaciÃ³n</a>formal de un&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anillo_(matem%C3%A1ticas)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anillo (matemÃ¡ticas)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">anillo</a>&nbsp;que dota al anillo de estructura de&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grupo_abeliano\" title=\"Grupo abeliano\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">grupo abeliano</a>, o la operaciÃ³n de un&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/M%C3%B3dulo_(matem%C3%A1ticas)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MÃ³dulo (matemÃ¡ticas)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">mÃ³dulo</a>que dota al mÃ³dulo de estructura de&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grupo_abeliano\" title=\"Grupo abeliano\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">grupo abeliano</a>. TambiÃ©n se utiliza a veces en&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teor%C3%ADa_de_grupos\" title=\"TeorÃ­a de grupos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">teorÃ­a de grupos</a>&nbsp;para representar la operaciÃ³n que dota a un conjunto de estructura de&nbsp;<a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grupo_(matem%C3%A1tica)\" title=\"Grupo (matemÃ¡tica)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">grupo</a>. En estos casos se trata de una denominaciÃ³n puramente simbÃ³lica, sin que necesariamente coincida esta operaciÃ³n con la suma habitual en nÃºmeros, funciones, vectores, etc.</p><p style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" id=\"img_1555867458859\" alt=\"operaciÃ³n matemÃ¡tica suma 3 + 2 = 5\"></p><br>', 10),
(7, 'resta', 'resta matemÃ¡ticas', '<p>La <i>resta</i> o la <b>sustracciÃ³n</b> es una <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aritm%C3%A9tica\" title=\"AritmÃ©tica\">operaciÃ³n de aritmÃ©tica</a> que se representa con el <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Signo_menos\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Signo menos\">signo (â€“)</a>,\r\n representa la operaciÃ³n de eliminaciÃ³n de objetos de una colecciÃ³n. Por\r\n ejemplo, en la imagen de la derecha, hay 5-2 manzanasâ€”significando 5 \r\nmanzanas con 2 quitadas, con lo cual hay un total de 3 manzanas. Por lo \r\ntanto, 5 â€“ 2 = 3. AdemÃ¡s de contar frutas, la sustracciÃ³n tambiÃ©n puede \r\nrepresentar combinaciÃ³n otras magnitudes fÃ­sicas y abstractas usando \r\ndiferentes tipos de objetos: <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_negativos\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros negativos\">nÃºmeros negativos</a>, <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fracci%C3%B3n\" title=\"FracciÃ³n\">fracciones</a>, nÃºmeros irracionales, <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vector\" title=\"Vector\">vectores</a>, decimales, funciones, matrices y mÃ¡s.\r\n</p><p>La sustracciÃ³n sigue varios patrones importantes. Es <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conmutatividad\" title=\"Conmutatividad\">anticonmutativa</a>, lo que significa que el cambio de la orden cambia el signo de la respuesta. No es <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asociatividad_(%C3%A1lgebra)\" title=\"Asociatividad (Ã¡lgebra)\">asociativa</a>, lo que significa que cuando se restan mÃ¡s de dos nÃºmeros, importa del orden en el que se realiza la resta. Restar <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/0_(n%C3%BAmero)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"0 (nÃºmero)\">0</a>\r\n no cambia un nÃºmero. La sustracciÃ³n tambiÃ©n obedece a reglas \r\npredecibles relativas a las operaciones relacionadas, tales como la <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suma\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Suma\">adiciÃ³n</a> y la <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplicaci%C3%B3n\" title=\"MultiplicaciÃ³n\">multiplicaciÃ³n</a>. Todas estas reglas pueden probarse, a partir de la sustracciÃ³n de nÃºmeros enteros y generalizarlas mediante los <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_reales\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros reales\">nÃºmeros reales</a> y mÃ¡s allÃ¡. Las <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operaci%C3%B3n_binaria\" title=\"OperaciÃ³n binaria\">operaciones binarias</a> generales que siguen estos patrones se estudian en el <a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%81lgebra_abstracta\" title=\"Ãlgebra abstracta\">Ã¡lgebra abstracta</a>.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><br>', 10),
(8, 'prueba', 'prueba', 'jjhjkhkjk<br>', 11);

