 0.5em 0px 1.3em 1.4em; width: auto; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); padding: 3px; background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250); font-size: 13.16px; text-align: center; overflow: hidden; width: 227px;\"><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Image-Al-Kit%C4%81b_al-mu%E1%B8%ABta%E1%B9%A3ar_f%C4%AB_%E1%B8%A5is%C4%81b_al-%C4%9Fabr_wa-l-muq%C4%81bala.jpg\" class=\"image\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/23/Image-Al-Kit%C4%81b_al-mu%E1%B8%ABta%E1%B9%A3ar_f%C4%AB_%E1%B8%A5is%C4%81b_al-%C4%9Fabr_wa-l-muq%C4%81bala.jpg/225px-Image-Al-Kit%C4%81b_al-mu%E1%B8%ABta%E1%B9%A3ar_f%C4%AB_%E1%B8%A5is%C4%81b_al-%C4%9Fabr_wa-l-muq%C4%81bala.jpg\" class=\"thumbimage\" data-file-width=\"240\" data-file-height=\"380\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(200, 204, 209); vertical-align: middle; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\" width=\"225\" height=\"356\"></a><div class=\"thumbcaption\" style=\"border: 0px; line-height: 1.4em; padding: 3px; font-size: 12.3704px; text-align: left;\">PÃ¡gina del libro<span>&nbsp;</span><i><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compendio_de_c%C3%A1lculo_por_reintegraci%C3%B3n_y_comparaci%C3%B3n\" title=\"Compendio de cÃ¡lculo por reintegraciÃ³n y comparaciÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">KitÄb al-mukhtaá¹£ar fÄ« á¸¥isÄb al-Å·abr wa-l-muqÄbala</a></i>, de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Juarismi\" title=\"\" style=\"text-decoration: underline; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Al-Juarismi</a>.</div></div></div><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">La palabra Â«Ã¡lgebraÂ» proviene del vocablo<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Idioma_%C3%A1rabe\" title=\"Idioma Ã¡rabe\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Ã¡rabe</a><span>&nbsp;</span>Ø§Ù„Ø¬Ø¨Ø±<span>&nbsp;</span><i>al-Å·abar</i><span>&nbsp;</span>(en Ã¡rabe dialectal por<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asimilaci%C3%B3n_(ling%C3%BC%C3%ADstica)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"AsimilaciÃ³n (lingÃ¼Ã­stica)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">asimilaciÃ³n progresiva</a><span>&nbsp;</span>se pronunciaba [alÅ·É›bÉ¾] de donde derivan los tÃ©rminos de las lenguas europeas), que se traduce como \'restauraciÃ³n\' o \'reponimiento, reintegraciÃ³n\'. Deriva del tratado escrito alrededor del aÃ±o 820&nbsp;d.&nbsp;C. por el matemÃ¡tico y astrÃ³nomo persa<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Juarismi\" title=\"Al-Juarismi\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Muhammad ibn Musa al-Jwarizmi</a><span>&nbsp;</span>(conocido como Al Juarismi), titulado<span>&nbsp;</span><i>Al-kitÄb al-mukhtaá¹£ar fÄ« á¸¥isÄb<span>&nbsp;</span><b>al-Å·arabi</b><span>&nbsp;</span>waË€l-muqÄbala</i>(<i><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compendio_de_c%C3%A1lculo_por_reintegraci%C3%B3n_y_comparaci%C3%B3n\" title=\"Compendio de cÃ¡lculo por reintegraciÃ³n y comparaciÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Compendio de cÃ¡lculo por reintegraciÃ³n y comparaciÃ³n</a></i>), el cual proporcionaba operaciones simbÃ³licas para la soluciÃ³n sistemÃ¡tica de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecuaci%C3%B3n\" title=\"EcuaciÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">ecuaciones</a><span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecuaci%C3%B3n_lineal\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"EcuaciÃ³n lineal\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">lineales</a><span>&nbsp;</span>y<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecuaci%C3%B3n_cuadr%C3%A1tica\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"EcuaciÃ³n cuadrÃ¡tica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">cuadrÃ¡ticas</a>. Muchos de sus mÃ©todos derivan del desarrollo de la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matem%C3%A1tica_en_el_islam_medieval\" title=\"MatemÃ¡tica en el islam medieval\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">matemÃ¡tica en el islam medieval</a>, destacando la independencia del Ã¡lgebra como una disciplina matemÃ¡tica independiente de la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometr%C3%ADa\" title=\"GeometrÃ­a\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">geometrÃ­a</a><span>&nbsp;</span>y de la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aritm%C3%A9tica\" title=\"AritmÃ©tica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">aritmÃ©tica</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%81lgebra#cite_note-5\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">5</a></sup>â€‹ Puede considerarse al Ã¡lgebra como el arte de hacer<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuenta_(matem%C3%A1ticas)\" title=\"Cuenta (matemÃ¡ticas)\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">cÃ¡lculos</a><span>&nbsp;</span>del mismo modo que en<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aritm%C3%A9tica\" title=\"AritmÃ©tica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">aritmÃ©tica</a>, pero con objetos matemÃ¡ticos<span>&nbsp;</span><i>no-numÃ©ricos</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Boyer_6-0\" class=\"reference separada\" style=\"line-height: 1em; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; margin-right: 0.6ch;\"><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%81lgebra#cite_note-Boyer-6\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none; white-space: nowrap;\">6</a></sup>â€‹</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">El adjetivo Â«<b>algebraico</b>Â» denota usualmente una relaciÃ³n con el Ã¡lgebra, como por ejemplo en<span>&nbsp;</span><i><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Estructura_algebraica\" title=\"Estructura algebraica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">estructura algebraica</a></i>. Por razones histÃ³ricas, tambiÃ©n puede indicar una relaciÃ³n con las soluciones de<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polinomio\" title=\"Polinomio\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">ecuaciones polinomiales</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/N%C3%BAmeros_algebraicos\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NÃºmeros algebraicos\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">nÃºmeros algebraicos</a>,<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extensi%C3%B3n_algebraica\" title=\"ExtensiÃ³n algebraica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">extensiÃ³n algebraica</a><span>&nbsp;</span>o<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expresi%C3%B3n_algebraica\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ExpresiÃ³n algebraica\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">expresiÃ³n algebraica</a>. Conviene distinguir entre:</p><ul style=\"margin: 0.3em 0px 0px 1.6em; padding: 0px; list-style-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 width=%225%22 height=%2213%22%3E %3Ccircle cx=%222.5%22 cy=%229%22 r=%222.5%22 fill=%22%23222%22/%3E %3C/svg%3E&quot;); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><b><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%81lgebra_elemental\" title=\"Ãlgebra elemental\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Ãlgebra elemental</a></b><span>&nbsp;</span>es la parte del Ã¡lgebra que se enseÃ±a generalmente en los cursos de matemÃ¡ticas.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 0.1em;\"><b><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/%C3%81lgebra_abstracta\" title=\"Ãlgebra abstracta\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">Ãlgebra abstracta</a></b><span>&nbsp;</span>es el nombre dado al estudio de las Â«estructuras algebraicasÂ» propiamente.</li></ul><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">El Ã¡lgebra usualmente se basa en estudiar las combinaciones de cadenas finitas de signos y, mientras que<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/An%C3%A1lisis_matem%C3%A1tico\" title=\"AnÃ¡lisis matemÃ¡tico\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">anÃ¡lisis matemÃ¡tico</a><span>&nbsp;</span>requiere estudiar lÃ­mites y sucesiones de una cantidad infinita de elementos.</p><br>', 10, 3);
INSERT INTO `foros` (`idforo`, `titulo`, `descripcion`, `contenido`, `idautor`, `idcurso`) VALUES
(3, 'INTEGRALES POR ', '', '<div><h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"IntroducciÃ³n\">IntroducciÃ³n</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Integral_m%C3%BAltiple&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: IntroducciÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">De la misma manera en que la integral de una funciÃ³n positiva<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle f(x)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/202945cce41ecebb6f643f31d119c514bec7a074\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"f(x)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 4.418ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>de una variable definida en un intervalo puede interpretarse como el Ã¡rea entre la grÃ¡fica de la funciÃ³n y el eje x en ese intervalo, la<span>&nbsp;</span><b>doble integral</b><span>&nbsp;</span>de una funciÃ³n positiva<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle f(x,y)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/29473ed0c4e838ac9dbe074535e507166c0e9101\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"f(x,y)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 6.607ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>de dos variables, definida en una regiÃ³n del plano xy, se puede interpretar como el volumen entre la superficie definida por la funciÃ³n y el plano xy en ese intervalo. Al realizar una \"integral triple\" de una funciÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle f(x,y,z)}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f5d48dce2c4341575269f1709237a2e18923237a\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"f(x,y,z)\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 8.729ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>definida en una regiÃ³n del espacio xyz, el resultado es un<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hipervolumen\" title=\"Hipervolumen\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">hipervolumen</a>, sin embargo es bueno notar que si<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle f(x,y,z)=1}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f4c4ea840cd139e57682ad1838bf974a9f315d84\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle f(x,y,z)=1}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 12.99ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>el resultado se puede interpretar como el volumen de la regiÃ³n de integraciÃ³n. Para integrales de Ã³rdenes superiores, el resultado geomÃ©trico corresponde a hipervolÃºmenes de dimensiones cada vez superiores.</p><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">La manera mÃ¡s usual de representar una integral mÃºltiple es anidando<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Signos_de_integraci%C3%B3n\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Signos de integraciÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">signos de integraciÃ³n</a><span>&nbsp;</span>en el orden inverso al orden de ejecuciÃ³n (el de mÃ¡s a la izquierda es el Ãºltimo en ser calculado), seguido de la funciÃ³n y los diferenciales en orden de ejecuciÃ³n. El dominio de integraciÃ³n se representa sobre cada signo de integral, o a menudo es abreviado por una letra en el signo de integral de mÃ¡s a la derecha:</p><blockquote style=\"font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; padding: 5px 10px; background-color: white; color: black; text-align: left; margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0.4em; margin-top: 0.2em; min-width: 50%;\"><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit;\"><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle iint ldots int _{mathbf {D} };f(x_{1},x_{2},ldots ,x_{n});mathbf {d} x_{1}mathbf {d} x_{2}!ldots mathbf {d} x_{n}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b59ca4f565ca09a183c38ff7cce705e5c6e5733e\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle iint ldots int _{mathbf {D} };f(x_{1},x_{2},ldots ,x_{n});mathbf {d} x_{1}mathbf {d} x_{2}!ldots mathbf {d} x_{n}}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -2.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 43.067ex; height: 5.676ex;\"></span></p></blockquote><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Es importante destacar que no es posible calcular la<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funci%C3%B3n_primitiva\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"FunciÃ³n primitiva\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">funciÃ³n primitiva</a><span>&nbsp;</span>o<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antiderivada\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Antiderivada\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">antiderivada</a><span>&nbsp;</span>de una funciÃ³n de mÃ¡s de una variable por lo que las integrales mÃºltiples<span>&nbsp;</span><i>indefinidas</i><span>&nbsp;</span>no existen.</p><h2 style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: normal; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-size: 1.5em; font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; line-height: 1.3; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span id=\"Definici.C3.B3n\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"DefiniciÃ³n\">DefiniciÃ³n</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\" style=\"user-select: none; font-size: small; font-weight: normal; margin-left: 1em; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1em; font-family: sans-serif; white-space: nowrap; unicode-bidi: isolate;\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-right: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">[</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Integral_m%C3%BAltiple&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Editar secciÃ³n: DefiniciÃ³n\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">editar</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\" style=\"margin-left: 0.25em; color: rgb(84, 89, 93);\">]</span></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0.5em 0px; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Una forma relativamente sencilla de definir las integrales mÃºltiples es mediante su representaciÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geom%C3%A9trico\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"GeomÃ©trico\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\">geomÃ©trica</a><span>&nbsp;</span>como la magnitud del espacio entre el objeto definido por la ecuaciÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle x_{n+1}=f(x_{1},...,x_{n})}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2459e4916262db13c9d13d599dab21df2296396e\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle x_{n+1}=f(x_{1},...,x_{n})}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 20.937ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>y una regiÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle T}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ec7200acd984a1d3a3d7dc455e262fbe54f7f6e0\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"T\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 1.636ex; height: 2.176ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>en el espacio definido por los ejes de las variables independientes de la funciÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle f}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/132e57acb643253e7810ee9702d9581f159a1c61\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"f\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 1.279ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>(si<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle T}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ec7200acd984a1d3a3d7dc455e262fbe54f7f6e0\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"T\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 1.636ex; height: 2.176ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>es una regiÃ³n cerrada y acotada y<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle f}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/132e57acb643253e7810ee9702d9581f159a1c61\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"f\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 1.279ex; height: 2.509ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>estÃ¡ definida en Ã©sta). Por ejemplo, si<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle n=2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/a02c8bd752d2cc859747ca1f3a508281bdbc3b34\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle n=2}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.338ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 5.656ex; height: 2.176ex;\"></span>, el volumen situado entre la superficie definida por<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle x_{3}=f(x_{1},x_{2})}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f25cdddf2de6bac3e2a5c90a3d2e96e5b70c4256\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" alt=\"{displaystyle x_{3}=f(x_{1},x_{2})}\" style=\"border: 0px; vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin: 0px; display: inline-block; width: 14.372ex; height: 2.843ex;\"></span><span>&nbsp;</span>y una regiÃ³n<span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px); overflow: hidden; position: absolute; width: 1px; height: 1px; opacity: 0;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{displaystyle T}</annotation></semantics></math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/ec7200acd984